*************************************************************************
**                                                                     **
**               Introduction to GPU Programming with GLSL             **
**                                                                     **
**                              README File                            **
**                                                                     **
*************************************************************************

    This application demo shows some basic functionalities of shaders
    using GLSL.  The demo was developed as a tutorial named:
    "Introduction to GPU Programming with GLSL"; for SIBGRAPI 2009
    conference: http://www.matmidia.mat.puc-rio.br/sibgrapi2009/.

Directories:

    bin/            :- output binaries
    include/        :- header files
    lib/            :- external libraries
        GL/         :- GLee (http://elf-stone.com/glee.php)
        glslKernel/ :- GLSL Kernel (http://code.google.com/p/lcgtk)
	arcball/    :- Arcball external code
    src/            :- source codes

Compile:

    -= Compile both programs =-

    $ make

    -= Compile only shaders or particles =-

    $ make bin/shaders

    $ make bin/particles

    -= Run programs going inside bin/ =-

    $ cd bin

    $ ./particles

    $ ./shaders

Mac OS X:

    We tested our code on a Mac Mini (MAC OS X 1.5 Leopard version)
    successfully.  Here are some hints in order to do this:

    -= Install missing packages using Mac Ports =-

    -= Install GLUT =-

    $ sudo port install glut

    -= Access website =-

    http://developer.apple.com/mac/library/samplecode/glut/index.html

    -= Download the zip, uncompress and follow ReadMe.txt =-

    -= Install GLEW =-

    $ sudo port install glew

    -= Change Makefile to add MAC_FLAG and MAC_LINK =-

